{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"Plan-review v4 PASS (0 blocking, 17 advisory) — design gated. (v3 was INDETERMINATE only due to a verify-step token-cap truncation, filed as bug spy-luge-wool; v4's tightened 7-AC form verified cleanly.) Advisory triage — all valid, folding into implementation:\n- [T9/#6] First deploy has no :prev image -> rollback skips gracefully if :prev absent (tag :prev only after a known-good run).\n- [T9/#10] Prune dangling review-bot image layers after a successful build (docker image prune -f scoped).\n- [T5b/#11] git fetch gets --timeout / a wrapping timeout so a hung fetch never holds the flock across timer fires.\n- [#12] Concrete health check: receiver /health endpoint + a synthetic review probe (assert the bot casts on a canary) — spec'd in the script.\n- [G1G2/#1,#2] make config-check must run in BOTH test.yml AND gerrit-verify.yaml (gerrit-verify mirrors the gates inline) so a malformed config fails the Verified gate.\n- [T3/#5] CORRECTION: the review-bot is a DOCKER container, not a systemd service — so the crash-loop storm guard is docker-compose restart policy (on-failure w/ max retries) + the deploy loop's SHA-keyed backoff, NOT systemd StartLimit (which only applies to the autodeploy oneshot itself). Will adjust.\n- [G1G2/#3,#14] materialize-g2p-config.sh refreshes the g2p bind-mount copy of replication.config; observability.sh gains the AUTODEPLOY_ERROR probe; name monitoring_autodeploy.tf.\n- [E1/#15] project.config == refs/meta/config terminology unified.\n- [T5e/#16] thresholds (2m cadence, 30s health timeout, backoff 60s/2/15m) as named constants at the top of autodeploy.sh.\nStarting the build with the lowest-risk piece: the CI config-validation gate (make config-check)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783078042731087001,"uuid":"7bc8cfce-ba3f-4565-b94d-f6169baf9450"}